        <h1>URGENT MANHUNT: 'Panda Bandit' Alfono Eludes Authorities After Daring Heist</h1>
        <div class="byline">By Anonymous Reporter | <span style="color: #cc0000; font-weight: 600;">EXCLUSIVE</span> | October 26, 2023</div>
        <p>Law enforcement agencies worldwide have launched a massive search for a notorious individual known only as 'Alfono', following a bizarre and audacious theft involving highly protected animals and an enormous quantity of vegetation.</p>
        <p>Sources close to the investigation confirmed today that Alfono is wanted in connection with the disappearance of three juvenile giant pandas from a secure facility under mysterious circumstances. Adding to the peculiarity of the crime, approximately 5000 kilograms (that's 5 metric tons!) of high-grade bamboo was also reported missing from the same location.</p>
        <div class="image-container">
            <img src="/Screenshot 2025-05-06 142850.png" alt="Roblox avatar profile of SG_Alfono" class="alfono-img">
            <div class="image-caption">Authorities have released an image of suspect Alfono, believed to be connected to the recent panda and bamboo theft. SOURCE: POLICE HANDOUT</div>
        </div>
        <p>Investigators are baffled by the motive behind such an unusual crime. "We've seen everything, but three pandas and five tons of bamboo? This is new territory," stated Detective Sergeant Patches O'Malley during a press conference earlier today. "We suspect Alfono may have specialized knowledge of panda dietary needs, or perhaps an extremely ambitious pet project."</p>
        <p>Alfono is described as being of average height, unremarkable appearance, and possessing an unsettlingly calm demeanor, according to vague witness accounts. Authorities caution the public not to approach Alfono, as his behavior is unpredictable and he may be heavily armed with bamboo shoots.</p>
        <p>Anyone with information regarding Alfono's whereabouts, or the location of the missing pandas and bamboo, is urged to contact the International Wildlife Crime Task Force immediately. A reward for information leading to his capture, and the safe return of the pandas, is being offered, though the amount of bamboo required for the reward is still under negotiation.</p>
        <p class="warning">CITIZEN ALERT: Secure all bamboo stocks! Report any large, slow-moving vehicles or suspicious activity involving leafy green material. DO NOT APPROACH ALFONO.</p>

